column1: # "Long-form" encoding of the complete PAD data
# Each word in the data is put on a separate line, and is given an unique ID in the first column.
# These IDs are also used in the alignment files.
# The column CONCEPT lists the meaning-designation as used in the original data.
# Because this is dialect data, almost all words with the same meaning are also cognate, but not all!
# Also, some cognate words were distinguished in the original data (e.g. "Äpfeln" and "Äpfelchen").
# There were also a few erroneous classifications (e.g. between "recht" and "lauter").
# Some words have been divided into separate cognate sets (e.g. various non-cognate words for "Dienstag").
# The column COUNTERPART lists the actual form as originally transcribed.
# The column CONCEPTID lists the numbers as used in the original data
# The column DOCULECT lists the short name of the village. See /data/doculects.csv for more info on each village.
# The column TOKENS lists a tokenization of the original transcription into phonetic units (according to the transcription!).
# The column COGID lists a separate ID for all words that are actually cognate. These IDs are summarized in the file /data/cognatesets.csv
